body:
@datariders I had the same issue. The problem here is gunicorn is binding to just `127.0.0.1` inside the container. The workaround is to pass host while starting your ui like `mlflow ui --host 0.0.0.0`. Or you can also go into `/app/mlflow/cli.py` and change the default host to `0.0.0.0`.

I did this and was able to access the UI from chrome on my host using `localhost:5000` or `127.0.0.1:5000`

Let me know if this works out for you.
